      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Gas Mark is a temperature scale used primarily in the UK and Ireland for gas ovens. It ranges from Â¼ to 10, with each number roughly corresponding to a 25Â°F increment starting from Gas Mark 1 = 275Â°F."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How accurate are home oven thermostats?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
